<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arthrocnemum</i> <i>subterminale</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Atriplex</i> <i>patula</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>prostrata</i>, <i>Batis</i> <i>maritima</i>, <i>Cotula</i> <i>coronopifolia</i>, <i>Cressa</i> <i>truxillensis</i>, <i>Cuscuta</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Grindelia</i> <i>stricta</i>, <i>Jaumea</i> <i>carnosa</i>, <i>Limonium</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Monanthochloe</i> <i>littoralis</i>, <i>Sarcocornia</i> <i>pacifica</i>, <i>Suaeda</i> <i>esteroa</i> and <i>Suaeda</i> <i>taxifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs and herbs < 30 cm; canopy is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Arthrocnemum subterminale</i> > 30% relative cover with other salt marsh plants (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal salt marshes. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Arthrocnemum subterminale</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

        
